metadata.name: Alien Stars #35
metadata.description:
This work celebrates the great achievement of the James Webb Space Telescope bringing to us infrared images of the most distant universe so far. Alien stars will soon be unveiled to us in different shapes and forms unknown to date.

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.

metadata.name: Breakdown #180
metadata.description:
The key to solving a difficult problem is to break it down into a series of smaller, more tractable, problems.

Here we start with a rectangular polygon. We shrink our polygon by some fixed amount (inset), and then pick a point inside it. We then send off rays in N evenly spaced directions and use these to split the polygon into N new polygons. Repeat the process, varying parameters such as how we pick our point or the angles of our projected rays, and see what emerges.

Press 'v' to download an svg output.

metadata.name: Dark Stars #1
metadata.description:
In astronomy, black holes are incredibly dense regions of space where the gravitational force is so strong that nothing, not even light, can escape from it. A black hole is literally a tear in the fabric of spacetime. Such a thing can only be created by the collapse of a massive star‚Äìor possibly by a dark star. 

In philosophical terms, a black hole is a place where everything is pulled into a single point. It is the end of all things; the mind becomes totalitarian, and the self is lost.

Dark stars and black holes may represent an ending‚Äìa finality‚Äìbut generative art is a beginning. Generative projects have the potential to change the way we think about art and life.

Art can be one way that our consciousness avoids falling into a black hole. By appreciating the beauty in nature, we can find hope and avoid becoming trapped in an endless abyss. 

So it is with generative art; from the darkness of a black hole, from the mystery of a dark star, new ideas and new ways of seeing the world are born.

Press ‚Äòs‚Äô to save the image.

metadata.name: CMYK:Split #59
metadata.description:
CMYK:Split uses code to blow apart the CMYK screens used to produce the printed portraits, then scale and position randomly on the X axis.

The four individual female portraits within this piece have been generated using AI.

Please Note: Once your hash-generated composition has been shown the piece will continue to create further infinite compositions.

metadata.name: strokes-1 #9
metadata.description:
A generative abstract painting using layers of strokes of different size, strength and color.

The painting is rendered by simulating one stroke at a time. The recipe is similar for all paintings. First, wide faint brush strokes cover the canvas with a background texture, then a few strong brush strokes give the piece some character. After that, very fine rapid strokes give the piece some interesting detail and finally, dabs of very short brush strokes are applied for additional sense of depth. 

The rendering takes some time. With large screen sizes, you get bigger pictures (for printing!), but the rendering is slower. 

Once the work is painted, you can hit 's' to save a png file. 

There are 7 different colour schemes.

metadata.name: DEBUGGERS #28
metadata.description:
Interactive generative painting made from points and lines in a stretchy pixelated mesh. Built with webgl and javascript. By @galoandstuff.

Click (or touch) and hold to apply wind force.
Press 's' to save PNG (live mode only).

metadata.name: Planetary Abstracts #127
metadata.description:
A hazy planet looms large in an alien solar system. The image is "drawn" over 1,000 iterations with colored pencils on textured paper. The final image takes about 40-50 seconds.

The image size is 1200x1200. Press 's' to save a screenshot or 'p' to pause and resume drawing.

Common features:
- 50 color palettes
- Planet size, full view to partial
- 3 to 8 moons
- 2 noise methods
- 4 color modes
- 3 focus areas (line thickness)
- Vertical or horizontal accent bars

Uncommon
- Monochrome color palette
- Mono with color highlights
- Mono with gold highlights

Rare
- Mono with dark background

metadata.name: My essence, My Connectible #85
metadata.description:
The 'My essence, My Connectible' collection expresses the essence of web3 human beings when we define ourselves not through a self-portrait but display our inner perception of our personality.

My Connectible is My Essence, it is as alive as I am, it is always in motion.

Features:

‚ö° 17 color skins /themes/: –°olor Sketch, X-Ray, Black Marble, –°oral, Pure Color, Marine, Vintage, Scheme, Chalks, Reverse, Jazz, Copper, Ball Pen, Grunge, Neon, Dusted Truffle, Violet. Each theme contains 1-7 palettes.

‚ö° Two background textures: either dots or lines.

‚ö° Three types of entities: —Åircles, triangles, and rhombuses. They have a core... or they don't.

‚ö° Dynamic number of blocks: 3x3, 4x4, 5x5, 6x6, 7x7.

Animation saving works in test mode (Chrome only): press 'open live' button, press 'S', wait 10-15 seconds. The saved GIF will open in a pop-up window or a new tab.

metadata.name: Slanted #80
metadata.description:
Fun little game, simple rules:
- start with a randomly sized grid
- pick 2 random cells
- recursively, every cell draw itself
- then it picks two of its neighbors for the next step

Some cells are drawn multiple times, some others are never picked up, but the process it's not completely random.
